article.description: Jordan Allen had 23 points as Rider got past Marist 75-64 on Sunday in a regular-season finale.
article.headline: Allen scores 23 to lead Rider past Marist 75-64
article.linkText: Allen scores 23 to lead Rider past Marist 75-64
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Jordan Allen had 23 points as Rider got past Marist 75-64 on Sunday in a regular-season finale. Allen hit 6 of 9 3-pointers. Anthony Durham had 13 points for Rider (16-14, 11-7 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Stevie Jordan added 13 points and seven rebounds. Brian Parker had 19 points for the Red Foxes (12-18, 7-11), who have now lost four games in a row. Ryan Funk added 16 points. Austin Williams had 11 points and six rebounds. The Broncs improve to 2-0 against the Red Foxes this season. Rider defeated Marist 86-85 on Jan. 27. The Broncs and the Red Foxes next take the floor in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Tournament. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
